*Security configuration

  The <<<SecurityFilterChain>>> is a standard Spring Security configuration — there is nothing
  OfficeFloor-specific about it.  The same configuration that works for a <<<@RestController>>>
  works unchanged for OfficeFloor YAML endpoints:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestsecurity/SecurityConfig.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  Spring Security's filter chain runs before OfficeFloor's handler interceptor, so unauthenticated
  requests to protected paths are rejected by Spring Security before they ever reach the service
  method.  No OfficeFloor configuration is involved.



